Class ChooseTemplate

java.lang.Object
Screen
ChooseTemplate
public class ChooseTemplate
extends Screen
Screen that handles the creation and presentation of the screen containing shapes that the user can select to choose a square, circular or triangular garden layout or drawing the perimeter manually.
Author:
Takiyah Price

  • Constructor Details

    • ChooseTemplate

      public ChooseTemplate​(Controller c, javafx.stage.Stage s)
      Constructor for ChooseTemplate that creates Buttons for choosing the shape of the garden and puts them on a new Scene. Each Button has an ImageView indicating its respective layout that will be created on click.

      public void mouseInside​(javafx.scene.shape.Shape s)
      Detects which template the mouse entered and changes its appearance by calling setHoverAffect() on the required template Shape.

    • setHoverEffect

      public void setHoverEffect​(javafx.scene.layout.HBox h, javafx.scene.shape.Shape s)
      Changes the background of the given HBox and the stroke color and width of the given Shape. To be called by mouseInside to update the template when hovered over.
      Parameters:
      h - the HBox containing the shape that the mouse entered.
      s - the Shape that the mouse entered.
      See Also:
      mouseInside(Shape s)

    • removeHoverEffect

      public void removeHoverEffect​(javafx.scene.layout.HBox h, javafx.scene.shape.Shape s)
      Resets the background of the given HBox and removes the stroke color of the given Shape. To be called by mouseOutside to update the template when the mouse exits the node.
      Parameters:
      h - the HBox containing the shape that the mouse exited.
      s - the Shape that the mouse exited.
      See Also:
      mouseOutside(Shape)

    • mouseOutside

    • mouseClicked

      public void mouseClicked​(javafx.scene.shape.Shape s)
      Updates the appearance of the HBox containing the template Shape that was clicked to communicate that it has been selected, and calls removeMouseClickedEffect on all other Shapes to keep only the most recent selection.
      Parameters:

    • removeMouseClickedEffect

      public void removeMouseClickedEffect​(javafx.scene.shape.Shape s)
      Removes the background and border set for mouse clicked for all other shapes besides the one passed in. To be called by mouseClicked to ensure that only one template is selected.
      Parameters:
      s - the template Shape that has been clicked.
